Introduction

Team 24 o'clock (Korean: 팀 24시; Japanese: チーム24時), also known as 24 o'clock, is a project boy group formed through the JTBC's reality-survival program 'Peak Time.' The group consists of B.A.P's Moon Jongup, XENO-T's Bjoo, B.I.G's Heedo, and ARGON's Gon.

During the airing of 'Peak Time,' Team 24 o'clock originally began as a five-member group, with BLACK6IX's Kim Hyunjae. However, the idol had to step down from the program due to school bullying accusations.
